#X text 1115 641 main algorithm;
#X text 1078 665 data transfer between processing and pure data;
#X text 1043 692 flucoma neural network and parameter mapping;
#X text 982 132 TIME (20-1000): controls the global delay time in milliseconds for every grain, f 59;
#X text 981 190 CUTOFF (5-10000): introduces a 24 dB/oct low pass filter, f 59;
#X text 981 301 MIX (0-1): Global dry/wet control for the device. 0% mix acts as a digital bypass. only the limiter stays active., f 59;
#X text 982 78 DELAY (0-1): dry/wet control to introduce stereo per-grain delay with randomised feedback, f 59;
#X text 982 231 PITCH (-2oct to +2oct): Determines the global pitch of the grains. this works in parallel with the random octave pitching inside the granular algorithm, f 59;
#X text 979 357 FREEZE (0 or 1): momentary freeze button engages the second buffer that traps the audio within a predetermined time frame and loops it indefinitely.;
#X text 981 432 TOUCH SCREEN (X/Y): The screen captures touch inputs via processing and sends them as X and Y data into pure data. This data gets used to control the fluid.mlpregressor inside the "network" subpatch. it is trained to represent and roughly remember certain states. instead of using this as a simple x/y pad for every parameter the regressor dynamically controls each one independently \, allowing for a variety of custom states to merge between \, without the repetitivness of a static \, linear XY pad., f 59;
#X coords 0 747 1 746 85 60 0;
